body:
It seems that this doesn't flag as an UNDRIVEN warning even though clk is undriven. Is it possible for Verilator's linter to determine that the clk signal is undriven in `a` and is not a port of module `a` so any uses of it further down in the hierarchy must be undriven? I haven't simulated this exact example, but I've done something just like this in a bigger design to determine whether `-Wwarn-UNDRIVEN` is useful and it doesn't seem to report any issue in this case.

```systemverilog
module a (
  output logic x
);
  logic clk;

  b b_inst (.clk, .x);

endmodule

module b (
  input logic clk,
  output logic x = '0
);

  always_ff @(posedge clk) begin
    x <= ~x;
  end

endmodule
```
